main event: A round, red object, the size of a baseball, was observed with a smooth, bright flight path in Wisconsin on 10 May 1956.
interesting points: Initially believed to be a meteorite due to its appearance and flight path.
The object was observed for two minutes.
It was observed using ground radar.
The report includes photographs of the object.
The sighting was possibly caused by the exhaust of a jet aircraft, according to comments.
result: prosaic explanation - possibly caused by the exhaust of a jet aircraft
sighted object: round, red object the size of a baseball
